### CSS Direction Handling
- Use Tailwind's built-in RTL support
- Add `dir="rtl"` to HTML elements when `lang === 'ar'`
- Use logical properties: `ms-` (margin-start), `me-` (margin-end)
- Avoid hardcoded `left`/`right` - use `start`/`end` instead

### Icon and Layout Mirroring
- Mirror directional icons (arrows, etc.) for Arabic
- Ensure proper text alignment: `text-right` for Arabic, `text-left` for English
- Handle form layouts and navigation appropriately

